REMARKS.content:
REMARKS:  Diagnostic horizons and features recognized in this series are:
ochric epipedon - the zone from the surface of the soil to a depth of 10 inches (A and E horizons);
argillic horizon - the zone from a depth of approximately 10 to 24 inches (Bt1 and Bt2 horizons);
fragipan - the zone from approximately 24 to 40 inches (2Bx1 and 2Bx2 horizons).
National Cooperative Soil Survey
U.S.A.
